label.value: Giemsa stain assay

definition.value: An assay that uses a Giemsa stain to characterize cells.

label.value: individual organism specimen

definition.value: A specimen composed of an individual organism to be studied in an investigation.

label.value: blood microbiology assay

definition.value: An organism detection assay that detects microorganisms in a blood specimen.

label.value: biopsy

definition.value: A specimen collection that obtains a sample of tissue or cell from a living multicellular organism body for diagnostic purposes by means intended to be minimally invasive.

label.value: image guided biopsy

definition.value: A biopsy which uses an imaging procedure to guide a needle biopsy.

label.value: computed tomography assisted biopsy

definition.value: A needle biopsy guided by real-time computed tomography (CT) scan images.

label.value: ultrasound-guided needle biopsy

definition.value: A needle biopsy guided by ultrasound visualization.

label.value: needle biopsy

definition.value: A biopsy that uses a hollow needle to extract cells.

label.value: fine needle aspiration biopsy

definition.value: A biopsy that uses a thin needle to extract cells.

label.value: core needle biopsy

definition.value: A biopsy that uses a hollow tube to collect a core of tissue.

label.value: surgical biopsy

definition.value: A biopsy involving a surgical incision into an organism to access the biopsy material.

label.value: abdominal wall fat pad biopsy

definition.value: A biopsy involving the collection of a small part of the abdominal wall fat pad.

label.value: tail biopsy

definition.value: A biopsy involving the collection of the tip of a mamallian tail.

label.value: bone marrow biopsy

definition.value: A biopsy where a small amount of bone and a small amount of fluid and bone marrow are collected.

label.value: skinpunch biopsy

definition.value: A biopsy that involves the collection of a cylinder of skin (including epidermis, dermis and superficial fat) using a punch tool.

label.value: cytometric bead array assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-15 production by T cells

definition.value: A cytometric bead array assay that detects interleukin-15 production by T cells.

label.value: cytometric bead array assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-16 production by T cells

definition.value: A cytometric bead array assay that detects interleukin-16 production by T cells.

label.value: in vivo assay measuring B cell epitope specific induction of hypersensitivity resulting from the adoptive transfer of epitope specific antibodies or B cells

definition.value: An efficacy of B cell epitope intervention experiment that detects a hypersensitivity response by monitoring skin reactions after adoptive transfer of epitope specific antibodies or B cells.

label.value: in vivo skin test assay measuring T cell epitope specific type IV hypersensitivity resulting from the adoptive transfer of epitope specific T cells

definition.value: An efficacy of T cell epitope intervention experiment that detects epitope specific type IV hypersensitivity after adoptive transfer of epitope specfic T cells.

label.value: in vivo assay measuring epitope specific proliferation of T cells resulting from the adoptive transfer of epitope specific T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific proliferation assay that is performed in vivo after adoptive transfer of epitope specfic T cells.

label.value: assay measuring epitope specific helper T cell enhancement of a B cell mediated immune response resulting from the adoptive transfer of epitope specific T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific helper activity assay that detects the ability of a T cell epitope to enhance an antibody response after adoptive transfer of epitope specfic T cells.

label.value: assay measuring epitope specific helper T cell enhancement of a T cell mediated immune response resulting from the adoptive transfer of epitope specific T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific helper activity assay that detects the ability of a T cell epitope to enhance a T cell response after adoptive transfer of epitope specfic T cells.

label.value: in vivo assay measuring epitope specific T cell killing resulting from the adoptive transfer of epitope specific T cells

definition.value: An in vivo cell killing assay that detects the killing of an antigen presenting cell (APC) by a T cell whose TCR recognizes an epitope presented by the APC after adoptive transfer of epitope specific T cells.

label.value: ELISA measuring epitope specific perforin release by T cells

definition.value: An enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay that detects epitope specific perforin release by T cells.

label.value: enrichment culture medium

definition.value: A culture medium that is designed to favor the growth of a particular microorganism or cells over others, enriching a sample for the microorganism or cells of interest.

label.value: case series design

definition.value: A study design that samples only subjects who have experienced a particular event (outcome or exposure). Such a design, in contrast to a cohort study, does not permit calculation of absolute risk as non-case subjects are not included.

label.value: massively parallel reporter assay

definition.value: An assay in which multiplexing the construction and interrogation of larger libraries of reporter constructs allows measurement of the transcriptional regulatory activities of thousands to hundreds of thousands of DNA sequences.

label.value: in vivo assay measuring a T cell epitope specific response after adoptive transfer of epitope specific T cells

definition.value: An efficacy of T cell epitope intervention experiment that is performed after adoptive transfer of epitope specfic T cells.

label.value: in vivo assay measuring a B cell epitope specific response after adoptive transfer of epitope specific antibodies or B cells

definition.value: An efficacy of B cell epitope intervention experiment that is performed after adoptive transfer of epitope specific antibodies or B cells.

label.value: in vivo assay measuring T cell epitope specific disease exacerbation resulting from the adoptive transfer of epitope specific T cells

definition.value: An efficacy of T cell epitope intervention experiment that uses a disease exacerbation in vivo intervention experiment after adoptive transfer of epitope specfic T cells.

label.value: vacuum-assisted biopsy needle

definition.value: A core biopsy needle integrated with a vacuum system which facilitates the collection of specimen material.

label.value: pseudovirus entry assay

definition.value: An assay that measures the entry in target cells of reporter viral particles that express an envelope protein of a different virus of interest.

label.value: glass bottle

definition.value: A container with a narrow neck that is made of glass.

label.value: glass bottle coated with insecticides

definition.value: A glass bottle that coated with material designed to control insects.

label.value: short interspersed nuclear elements polymerase chain reaction

definition.value: A polymerase chain reaction that amplifies short interspersed nuclear elements (SINEs).

label.value: nested polymerase chain reaction

definition.value: A polymerase chain reaction with modification intended to reduce non-specific binding in products due to the amplification of unexpected primer binding sites. The nested polymerase chain reaction (PCR) involves the use of two primer sets and two successive PCR reactions. The first set of primers are designed to anneal to sequences upstream from the second set of primers and are used in an initial PCR reaction.

label.value: immunoelectrophoresis

definition.value: An electrophoresis that separates and characterize proteins based on reaction with antibodies.

label.value: counter current immunoelectrophoresis

definition.value: An electrophoresis in which antigen and antibody move in opposite directions and form precipitates in the area between the cells where they meet in concentrations of optimal proportions.
